\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1.1}{\ignorespaces Moment maps of Per-emb-2 observed in HC$_3$N (10--9). Left: moment 0 (integrated intensity) map. Right: moment 1 (intensity-weighted mean velocity) map. The blue cross marks is used as the reference center for defining positional offsets and for subsequent points extraction method and model fitting. }}{5}{figure.caption.8}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1.2}{\ignorespaces Moment maps of Per-emb-50. Left: moment 0 (integrated intensity) map. Right: moment 1 (intensity-weighted mean velocity) map. The cross (white in moment 0 and blue in moment 1) defines the origin of the coordinate system for points extraction method and modeling. }}{6}{figure.caption.9}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1.3}{\ignorespaces Moment maps of HL~Tau. Left: moment 0 (integrated intensity) map. Right: moment 1 (intensity-weighted mean velocity) map. The white cross in the moment 0 map and the red cross in the moment 1 map defines the reference center for the coordinate system used in the analysis. }}{6}{figure.caption.10}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1.4}{\ignorespaces Moment maps of S~CrA. Left: moment 0 (integrated intensity) map. Right: moment 1 (intensity-weighted mean velocity) map. The blue cross marks the adopted stellar position, which is used as the reference center for positional offsets and subsequent analysis. The dashed circle represent the masked region for modeling. }}{7}{figure.caption.11}%
